{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696404/1930122301/0807.xml":{"full_text":"Financial Market News, Stocks, Bonds, Commodities and Comment\nGASH RESERVES\nAID STABILITY\nDFBANKS\nGrowth of Savings Accounts\nShows Minimum Slump\nEffects in Washington\nThe soundness of financial in\nstitutions in the District of Colum\nbia is emphasized by the absolute\nconfidence placed in the various\nbanks and trust companies scat\ntered throughout the city.\nSubstantial cash reserves, able\nmanagement and competent\njudgment of the banking busi\nness has enabled Washington fi\nnancial houses to forge to the\nfront so that at this time of \u2022de\npression throughout the entire\nUnited States they hold a fore\nmost position in the institutions\nhandling the funds of the Nation.\nAnother factor that must be\nconsidered in the local banking\na field is the fact that there is not\n1' as much unemployment here as\nin other sections of the country.\nThe majority of citizens of the\nDistrict are either employed by the\nGovernment or are dependent\nupon Government employees for\ntheir income.\nStores and other commercial\ninstitutions here are assured of\na steady income due to the fact\nthat the government pay is al\nways at hand when planned for.\nI In other cities throughout the\nUnited States, especially those in\nwhich large manufacturing plants\nare located there is a great deal\nof depression, due to the fact\nthat these organizations have\nbeen compelled to retrench and\nin so doing have been forced to\nlay off some of their workers.\nThis has worked hardships that\nare not experienced in the Dis\ntrict of Columbia.\nA sure sign of the fact that\ndepression in the District is\nlimited, bankers say, is the fact\nthat after payment of the Christ\nmas savings accounts for this\nyear a great number of the\nchecks were used in starting\nothers while savings accounts\nwere greatly swelled through de\nposits of Christmas checks.\nThe bankers point out that if\nthe depression was as rife as\nalarmists would have us believe\nthere would be no such growth\nof deposits and Christmas ac\ncounts.\nGeorge Bowie Chipman. resi\ndent partner of the stock Ex\nchange firm of Harriman 8c Co.\nhere, is en route to Miami where\nhe will spend Christmas. He\nis accompanied by his wife. They\nwin return to Washington after\nNew Year.\nDirectors of the Bank of\nBethesda have declared the regu\nlar semiannual dividend of 3\nper cent on the capital stock of\nthe institution. An extra dividend\nof 1 per cent was also voted. Both\ndividends are payable December\n31 to holders of record Decem\nber 20.\nA 5 per cent Christmas bonus\nfor employes and officers of the\nWashington Savings Bank was\nvoted at a recent meeting of the\nboard of] directors of the institu\ntion.\nDividends of many local stock\nIssues will be paid within the\nnext few days. The list of pal\nments include many bank stocks.\nIn addition to authorization of\nthe regular payments, many sub\nstantial disbursement have been\nvoted. Some of these take the\nform of an extra dividend, while\nothers are Christmas bonuses for\nemployes and officers of the or\nganizations.\nALCDITBATES\nAUTHORIZED\nThe Interstate Commerce Com\nmission today authorized certain\nrailroads to establish transconti\nnental freight rates on alcohol,\nother than denatured or wood,\nin bond, in tank cars, dependent\nupon the value declared in writ\ning by the shipper or agreed\nupon in writing.\nThe commission said it did\nnot approve the reasonableness\nof any rates or valuations that\nmight be filed under the author\nity given. Such rates and valu\nations are to be subject to pro\ntest, complaint, investigation and\ncorrection if found to be in con\nflict with any provision of the\nlaw.\nChicago to Sell New\n$10,007,000 Issue\nUpholding of the law of the\nState Legislature by the Supreme\ncourt of Illinois, under which $12,-\n000,000 of 5 per cent water fund\nrevenue bonds, due variously on\nJanuary 1, 1934, to 1948 were au\nthorized, the city of Chicago\nwill soon place on the market\n$10,997,000 of these bonds.\nIt is understood a syndicate\nheaded by Halsey, Stuart Co.,\nwill market the issue, /which ma\ntures as follows: $197,000 on\nJanuary 1, 1934; $250,000 on\nJanuary 1, 1935; sso,ooo*on Jan\nuary 1,1936; $250,000 on January\n1, 1137; $250,000 on January 1,\n1935, and $1,000,000 annually\nfrom January 1, 1930, to 1948,\nNew York Bond Market\n(Furnizhed by W. B. Hibbs Co.)\n(toverHnent Bonds\nLiberty 3 %\u2022.....i. 10L3B\nLiberty Ist cv 4%\u25a0 102.3*\nLiberty 4th 4%\u00ab.. 103.13\nTreasury 4%z............-.nr...... 112.0\nTreasury 4a 103.0\nTreasury Treasury 3%a 106.10\nDomestic Bonds\ninner Agri Chem 7Rs 102,6\nAmer Smelters Os 102\nAmer Sugar 103\nAmer Tel Tel 65.,.. 101%\nAmer Tel Tel 4Rs eV 122%\nAmer Tel Tel 5s S F 104%\nAmer Tel Tel 5%a 107\nAmer Water Works 65........... 101\nAnglo-Chll Nitrates is 67%\nArmour of Del 5%s 74\nAtchison Topeka ASF 45....... *7\nAtchison Topeka S F 4%z 112%\nAtlantic Refining 6s 102%\nBaltimore ft Ohio Ist 4s *6\nBaltimore ft Ohio 4 Via cv 92%\nBaltimore ft Ohio 5s 101\nBaltimore Ohio 05............. 10,%\nBal to Cc Ohio A 8 W 101\nBell Tel Pa 6s B 106%\nBoston Maine Be 97%\nBrooklyn Man Trans 6s A *7%\nBrooklyn Union Gas Sa 103\nCalifornia Petroleum s Vis \u20193B 100%\nCanadian Pacific 4%s \u201946.., 98%\nCanada Northern Ry 7s \u20194O 110%\nCentral Pae Ist Ref 4s \u201940........ 94%\nChesapeake ft Ohio 4%s '3O A,... 98%\nChesapeake Corp 5s \u201947.. 95%\nChi Northwestern 4%s cv 87\nChi it Northwestern 6Vis \u201936 106%\nChicago Burl ft Quincy 4%z \u201977 A 98%\nChi Buri ft Quincy Bes 6s-\u20197l. 75%\nChicago East Illinois 6s *51...... 31%\nChi Great Western 4s \u201959 64\nChi MH St P 4%s 91%\nChi Mil St P 4 Pac 5s \u201975........ 68\nChi Mil St P Pao adj 6a 2000... 26%\nChi Rock Island 4s \u2019BB FD 97%\nChi Rock Island 4%s \u201963.. 89\nChile Copper 6s '47 88\nClev Cin Chi St L 5s D 102%\nCleveland Un 