et\nBy LEWIS HANEY,\nDirector New York University Burcsui\nat Business Research and Former\nEconomist of Federal Trade\nCommission.\n1 The market appears to be\nrounding off prior to a \"second\nary\u201d decline. How far such a\nreaction may go is the big ques-\ntion. That it will come in some\nr form is a practical certainty, but\nwhether it will be dull and fail\nto touch the previous low level,\nor will be severe and break\nthrough, no one can know.\nIn any case, do not buy now.\nThe rally is nearly, if not quite.\nover. It Is the part of \u2018wisdom\nto wait until we see how the\nmarket stands up under the\npressure it must soon meet.\nThere is still over-extended fi\nnancial interests which may not\n1 be able to carry their present\n1 loads. This means a possibility\nof further liquidation, which may\ncome out on a little reaction.\nTherefore, wait and see. If the\nnext reaction is a minor oiie\nwhich does not lose more than\nhalf the ground gained on the\nrally, we may become more opti\nmistic. But if it brings out\nheavy liquidation again, we will\nknow that the bear market is\nnot over.\nMust Settle Down\nAbove all. remember this:\nThere will be no basis for confi\ndent buying of stocks until the\nmarket finally and definitely\u2019\n\u201csettles down.\u201d As long as it\njumps around the way it. still\ndoes, it has not become normal.\nA period of prolonged quiet and\ndullness, with very narrow fluc\ntuations that buying sound stocks\nhas become safe.\nLast week the averages made a\nnet gain of between three and\nfour points. The trading indus\ntrial stocks were about five points\nhigher at the close than a week\nago. The rails averaged two\nand one-half points higher. Utili\nties rallied sharply.\nIt is specially to be noted that\nge bond market turned up. and\nis is probably the most hopeful\nindication that has been seen for\na long time. The bond averages\nrose for three days in succession.\nThe rise was broad and brought\na net gain on the week of between\none and two full points. It can\nalso be said that a great deal of\niHlghf Low I Last\nMohawk Hud\" 7s id ptd| *4 *4 I*4\nNat Amer. 4%| 4%| 4%\nNat Aviation r 3%| I%| 3%\nNat Bond ft Share..*..l 27%| 3T%| 37%\nNat Food 8..|\nNat Fuel Gas.2l I 19%| 21\n-.Nat Inv 4%| 4%| 4%\nNat Short T Seo ft..... II IB II\nNew Eng Pwr pf..\u00ab... 7* 7* 7*\nNew Haven Clock I 8 8\nN V Hamburg 24% 28% 26%\nNewmont Mln 41 41% 41%\nNiag ft Hude Pow... 9 9%\nNlag Muds P A war... 1% 1% 1%\nNiag Hude -P B war... 4% 4% 4%\nNiagara Shr of Md.... 6% 4% 8%\nNiles Bern Po 20% 20% 20%\nNoma Electric 5% 6% 6%\nNoranda Mine 13% 13% 13%\nNo Ind Pub Ser pf.... *5% 95% 95%\nNor Sta Pw A cu pf.. 99 99 99\nPacific Gas pf 26% 26% 26%\nPacific W Oil. 7% 7% 7%\nPantepec OH 1% 1% 1%\nPennroad vtc 5% 5% 1%\nPeoples Lt A..*...... 1* 1* U\nPilot Radio A........ 3 2% 2%\nPitney Bowee 1% 1% 6%\nPitts Forging 8% 1%\nPittsb Pl G! 34% 34 34%\n'Polymet Mfg 1% 1% 1%\nPowdr ft A1ex......... 31% 21% 25%\nPrince ft Whitley\nPrince ft Whit pf.... 14% 14% 14%\nProducers Royalty.... 4 3% 3%\nPrudential Inv 7% 7% 7%\nPublic Utilities ww... 6 5% 6\nPublic Utilities w\nPyrene Mfg 4%| 6%\nP S of N 11l rts 11% 15% 15%\nRwy ft Util 1nv.....J 6% 6%|\nRalnb Lu B .....1 1% 1% |l%\nRaytheon Mfg... I 4 4 4\nReliable Storea 8 8\nReliance Inti Corp A..1 2% 2% 2%\nReliance Manar I 3% 3%J 8%\nReybarn Co I 1% 1% 1%\nSt Regie Pap I 12% 13 12\nSaxet Co I 6% 6% 6%\nSchldtter-Zander pfd.. I 6 I 4 6\nSchulte United I 1% 11%\nSecurities Corp new...l 17% 17% 17%\nSelected Indus I 2% 2% 2%\nSelect\nSelby Shoe 11 11 11.\nSentry Control 1% 1% 1%\nShenand cv pf 30% 30% 30%\nSilica Gel vtc 4% 4% 4%\nSouth Penn Oil 19%! 18% 18%\nS Cal Ed pf A 28%l 28% 28%\nSouth .Corp 2%l 2%| 2%\nSouthland Royalty 7%l 7%l 7%\n.S W Dairy Prod I%| I%| 1%\nSpiegel M R 6%s pf.. 17%l IT%I 17%\n8t OH of Ind 34 I 33 I 34\nSt 011 of Ky 19%f 19%1 19%\n82 QU of Ohio 44 I 44 I 44\nStein Cosmetic 3%1 2%i 8%\nSwift Internet 36% I 35 I 36%\nSwift ft Co new....... 27 I 27 