 most-\nr ly been in stocks in which there\nwas a large short interest and a\n5 small floating supply.\nj s\u2014The market is mixed and\nt shows many divergent trends,\nwith the old leaders not doing\nas wett as many more specula-\ntive issues.\nI The holidays lie ahead, and the\ni speculative forces may be mod\nerated for a few days, postponing\nthe test until after Christmas, it\nseems best, however, it be pre\npared for another setback.\nr '\"\"J 1\nW l B. HIBBS CO. i\nThe ONLY New York Stock Exchange House\nHaving Its Main Office in Washington\nM E M B ER S I\nNew York Stock Exchange \"i\n\u2022_ Boston Stock Exchange 4\nPhiladelphia Stock Exchange Z.\nWashington Stock Exchange\nNew York Cotton Exchange\nChicago Board of. Trade\nAmerican Bankers Association\nDistrict Bankers Association k\nHIBBS BUILDING\nNational 0540 WASHINGTON, D. C.\nt-\nG.lO. NET FOR 1\n11 MONTHS 15'\n54.14 SHARE\nRailway Shows Decrease of y\n24 Cents Over Figures Re\nported for 1929 Period\nChesapeake and Ohio Railway\nreports for the 11 months ended\nNovember 30 showed a net In\ncome of $37,757,339, equal, after H\ndividend requirements on 1,518 n\nshares of 6*4 per cent preferred\nstock, to $4.14 a share on 7,655,- m\n048 common shares, compared to of\n$40,577,529, or $4.37 a share in\nlike 1939 period, computed on the <r\nsame common share basis. No\nvember net income totaled s3,* st\n286,226, against $3,722,897 in No\nvember, 1929. q\nSOUTHERN RWY. SYSTEM\u2014\nGross for second week in Decern\nber amounted to $2,576,411\nagainst $3,284,826 in like 1929\nweek. From January 1 to Decern- 7\nber 14, gross was $149,291,382\ncompared with $181,911,064 in -Jx\ncorresponding 1929 period.\nMOBILE OHIO gross for\nsecond week in December J?\namounted to $208,459 against\n$288,018 in similar 1929 week. 7\nFrom January 1 to December 14\ngross was $13,475,377 compared r*\nwith $16,716,476 in correspond- J\u2019\ning 1929 period.\nILLINOIS CENTRAL SYSTEM\nNovember gross is estimated at\nabout $10,800,000 against $14;350,-\n208 in November, 1929. Eleven\nmonths ended November 30;-\nshowed estimated gross of $137,*\n591,000 compared with $166,927,-\n911 in similar 1929 period. n\nAMERICAN ICE CO.\u2014 Novem* r<*\nber net earnings totaled $174,077, to\nafter interest, but before Federal-fft\ntaxes and depreciation, against hr\n$250,045 in November, 1929. Net\nearnings for 11 months, ended\nNovember 30 were $5,699,002, 5\ncompared with $5,528,475 in cor\nresponding 1929 period.\nCHICAGO LIVESTOCK\nHog*\u2014Receipt*, 34.00*; maiket 10\ncent* lower; top. 88J18; bulk. 86.75@8;\nheavyweight. 17.58@7.10; Mellum weight,\n87.7008: lightweight. \u00bb7.85\u00a91; light\nlights. 87.90@S:10; packing bows, $6.58\n7.25; pigs. 87.50@8.10; holdovers, 4.000.\nCattle\u2014Receipts. 8.000; market steady.\nCalves: Receipts, 2,000; market steady, -w\nBeef steers: Good and choice, 8110\n12.75: common and medium. 87010.50<\nyearitnga, 87014. Butcher cattle: Heifu\nera *5012; row*, 847.50; bulla, 8507.50;\ncalve*. *7@lo; feeder steers. 8608.75} 13\nStocker steers. 85.5008.50; Stocker cowg t\nand heifers, 84@7.50.\nSheep\u2014Receipts, 18,000: market steady.\nMedium and choice lambe, 87.50@8.50;\ncnllsand common, 8307; yearlings, 85-50 Tt*\n@6.75; common and choke ewes, 820\n3.75; feeder lambs, 86@7.50.\nAll Inactive\nSecurities\nBought, Sold, Quoted\nJohn W. Welch Ce. Inc.\nEstablished 1021 K\n917 15th St. N. W. m\n\n(Wo epecltdize in finding\nmarket J SB\nPhone District 5952\n-a\nBrokerage Service\nfor Securities and\nCommodities\nFENNER 3\nBEANE A\nWASHINGTON, D. C;\nJ. D. MOTHERSHED W. E. LEWIS\nManagkm\n1430 K Street, N. W.\nPhone Nation*! 7000 4*\nMEMBERS\nNew York Stock Exchange\nand\nPrincipal Commodity Exchanges ',-T\nPrivate Wires to A\nNew York, New Orleans, Chicago\n21","height":"30081","width":"24174"}}
